Once you start getting to the point where you need to handle passing data between multiple components then I would consider using [Vuex][1] in order have a global component state that is accessible from all of your components.

Basically you can then create a totally separate &quot;store&quot; to hold your app&#39;s state (data):

```
const store = new Vuex.Store({
  state: {
    count: 0
  },
  mutations: {
    increment (state) {
      state.count++
    }
  }
})
``` 

And then from within each component, you can:

 - Use &quot;getters&quot; to read data from the store
 - Use &quot;actions&quot; to dispatch async functions that will &quot;mutate&quot; the store

e.g:

```
store.commit(&#39;increment&#39;) // this is a mutation
console.log(store.state.count) // -&gt; 1
```

  [1]: https://vuex.vuejs.org/

